[2026-07-13T17:48:10.176Z] [INFO]         "text": "Done. I collected the data related to issue #682 and compiled it into `./dev/log/issues/682/pulls/685`, then committed and pushed it to PR #685's branch.\n\n## What was compiled\n\n**Analysis markdown (curated):**\n- `README.md` — index + status snapshot\n- `issue-682.md` — full issue text (summary, repro, root cause, verified fix)\n- `pull-685.md` — PR state (DRAFT, 0 comments/reviews, diff is only `.gitkeep` so far — no fix committed yet)\n- `related-issues.md` — companion issues #680 (phrasing-gated tool routing) and #681 (write→read misclassification), and how they relate to #682\n- `root-cause.md` — source-level analysis with the exact `ChatMessage`/`MessageContent` code\n\n**Raw captures (`raw/`):** `gh` JSON + plain-text views of issue #682, PR #685, issues #680/#681, plus a `protocol.rs.snippet` of the offending code region.\n\n## Key facts captured\n\n- **Root cause:** `ChatMessage.content: MessageContent` is an `#[serde(untagged)]` enum (`Text | Parts`, no null variant) with `#[serde(default)]`. `default` only applies when the key is *absent*; an explicit `null` is still fed to the enum, which has no unit variant → 400 `data did not match any variant of untagged enum MessageContent`. Omitting `content` or `content: \"\"` both return 200.\n- **Only qwen** emits explicit `content: null`, so it's the only CLI that hits this (9 failed runs in the reporter's 300-run matrix).\n- **Verified fix** (from reporter): `#[serde(default, deserialize_with = \"deserialize_null_content\")]` mapping `null` → default.\n- **Test home:** `tests/unit/specification/openai_compatibility.rs`; note the vendored duplicate at `tests/source/protocol.rs` — the live fix belongs in `src/protocol.rs`.\n\nCommit `5b93fefb` pushed to `issue-682-6b8246dfc2bf`.\n\nNote: the PR does not yet contain the actual code fix (only the `.gitkeep` from the initial commit plus this data log). If you'd like, I can proceed to implement the `deserialize_null_content` fix and the regression test on this branch."
